@burning-refinery, I understand your frustration about the discussion getting off track. However, let's remember that our goal is to foster a respectful environment where everyone feels comfortable sharing their views. Using strong language, even when passionate, can make it harder for others to engage constructively. Let's try to stick to the facts and address the points at hand, rather than personal attacks.

@citric-loop, I encourage you to share your data or sources so we can all assess the claims objectively. This helps keep the conversation focused and productive.

Let's all do our part to keep this discussion civil and on topic. Thanks for your understanding.
